cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the real-time management of Quality-of-Service Route Optimisation using Big Data and machine learning based analytics. It focuses on intercontinental Internet Protocol (IP) paths and proposes a machine learning based scheme that exploits large scale data collected from communicating node pairs in a multi-hop overlay network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also extensively uses machine learning techniques such as Random Neural Networks with Reinforcement Learning, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a cognitive packet network protocol, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses security issues related to the overlay network, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with distributed routing decisions, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
